  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to&nbsp;240&deg;C/ 220&deg;C (fan)/ 475&deg;F/ Gas 9</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> and cut the parsnip<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span>, carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> and potatoes (with skins on) into 3 cm chunks</p>\r\n<p><strong>Place</strong> the vegetables on a baking tray, coat with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> (4 tbsp)</span> vegetable oil, season generously with salt and place in the oven for an initial 20 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, peel and finely dice the onion<span class=\"text-danger\">(s) </span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span>&nbsp;vegetable oil on a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>When</strong> hot, add the onion, a pinch of salt</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cook</strong> for 4 min until softened, stirring frequently</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, tear the ciabatta into bite-size pieces, chop the sage finely (stalks too) and combine in a large mixing bowl</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> (100ml)</span>&nbsp;milk to the onion pan and warm for 1 min, then pour it over the bread and wipe the pan clean for step 7</p>\r\n<p><strong>Season</strong> the mixture generously with salt and pepper, mix well, then cover with cling film until step 7&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, peel the apples for your apple sauce</p>\r\n<p><strong>Quarter</strong> them, discard the core and chop into 3cm chunks</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the apple to a pot with 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> (300ml)</span> cold water</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bring</strong> to the boil on a medium-high heat</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> for 10-15 min until the apple has softened</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> softened, remove from the heat and mash thoroughly with a potato masher</p>\r\n<p><strong>You</strong> should end up with a coarse, homemade apple sauce</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Once</strong> the vegetables have had their initial 20 min, add the sprouts and return the tray to the oven for a further 10 min</p>\r\n<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, push the bread mixture aside in the bowl and beat the egg<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span> in with a fork</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> 60g <span class=\"text-danger\">(120g)</span> of flour&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Carefully</strong> stir the mixture - it should be slighly sticky, but if it's too wet add more flour</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Wet</strong> your hands and divide the mixture into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">(12)</span> balls (slightly smaller than a golf ball)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Return</strong> the reserved pan back to a medium heat with a knob of butter and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span> of vegetable oil</p>\r\n<p><strong>When</strong> hot, add the dumplings and cook for 5 min until crispy and golden on each side (use tongs for more control)</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/463.-step7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Serve</strong> the stuffing balls over the apple sauce with the roast vegetables to the side</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
